author: NASS
description:
I used a new colorization technique, fully restored and created immersive sound design for this rare footage of Victorian, London 1900s. This new version brings to life powerful scenes from a bustling capital — including busy London streets, traffic passing in front of the Bank of England and Mansion House, and a striking view of London’s East End from down Middlesex Street

Video Restoration Process:
✔ FPS boosted to 60 frames per second 
✔ Image resolution boosted up to HD 
✔ Improved video sharpness and brightness 
✔ Colorized only for the ambiance (not historically accurate)
✔added sound only for the ambiance
✔restoration:(stabilisation,denoise,cleand,deblur) 
✔face restoration

Please, be aware that colorization colors are not real and fake, colorization was made only for the ambiance and do not represent real historical data.

B&W Video Source: BFI (Free) - Walturdaw Company
